WEBVTT

1
00:12:24.445 --> 00:12:26.196
Sure do love you.

2
00:12:28.032 --> 00:12:29.824
- Morning.
- Good morning, Mrs. MacNeil.

3
00:12:29.992 --> 00:12:31.910
- How are you today?
- Fine, thank you.

4
00:12:32.078 --> 00:12:33.370
That's good.

5
00:12:33.537 --> 00:12:36.289
It's okay, I've got it. Thanks.

6
00:12:36.457 --> 00:12:39.000
- Good morning, madam.
- Good morning, Karl.

7
00:12:39.168 --> 00:12:43.088
Oh, Karl, we've got rats in the attic.
You'd better get some traps.

8
00:12:43.255 --> 00:12:46.591
- Rats?
- I'm afraid so.

9
00:12:46.759 --> 00:12:48.051
But the attic is clean.

10
00:12:48.219 --> 00:12:49.970
All right, then, we've got clean rats.

11
00:12:50.138 --> 00:12:53.432
- No, no. No rats.
- I just heard them, Karl.

12
00:12:53.600 --> 00:12:54.850
Maybe plumbing.

13
00:12:55.018 --> 00:12:58.187
Yeah, or maybe rats.
Now, will you just get the traps?

14
00:12:58.355 --> 00:12:59.605
Yes, I go now.

15
00:12:59.773 --> 00:13:01.649
Don't go now.
The stores aren't open yet.

16
00:13:01.817 --> 00:13:03.567
- I'll go see.
- They're closed!

17
00:13:04.361 --> 00:13:06.201
<i>In the group over here...</i>

18
00:13:06.363 --> 00:13:08.614
<i>...I need a priest, a nun
and two students.</i>

19
00:13:10.158 --> 00:13:13.119
<i>That's what we want.
That's exactly what we want.</i>

20
00:13:16.623 --> 00:13:18.624
Burke. Oh, Burke.

21
00:13:18.792 --> 00:13:20.626
- Is this scene really essential?
- Chris.

22
00:13:20.794 --> 00:13:22.586
Just consider if we can do without it.

23
00:13:22.754 --> 00:13:25.589
Take a look at this damn thing.
It just doesn't make sense.

24
00:13:25.757 --> 00:13:29.635
It's plain. You're a teacher of the college.
You don't want the building torn down.

25
00:13:29.803 --> 00:13:33.056
- Come on. I can read, for Christ's sake.
- Well, what's wrong?

26
00:13:33.224 --> 00:13:35.475
Well, why are they tearing
the building down?

27
00:13:35.643 --> 00:13:38.645
Shall we summon the writer?
He's in Paris, I believe.

28
00:13:38.813 --> 00:13:39.980
- Hiding?
- Fucking.

29
00:13:43.401 --> 00:13:45.652
Scene 39: Hotel. Take four.

30
00:13:45.820 --> 00:13:48.655
<i>All right. Hustle, background. And action.</i>

31
00:13:48.823 --> 00:13:50.423
<i>Hasn't there been enough killing?</i>

32
00:13:52.034 --> 00:13:53.535
<i>Is this your campus?</i>

33
00:13:55.163 --> 00:13:57.998
<i>Get the Defense Department
off this campus!</i>

34
00:14:00.001 --> 00:14:01.835
<i>It's our school!</i>

35
00:14:02.003 --> 00:14:04.004
<i>- You have no rights!</i>
- Hypocrite!

36
00:14:04.172 --> 00:14:06.131
<i>Military complex, man!</i>

37
00:14:06.299 --> 00:14:08.049
<i>And action, Chris.</i>

38
00:14:08.217 --> 00:14:10.260
<i>I've seen enough killing in my lifetime!</i>

39
00:14:12.014 --> 00:14:13.931
<i>There's no need for it!</i>

40
00:14:16.310 --> 00:14:19.312
<i>That's right! That's right!</i>

41
00:14:20.439 --> 00:14:23.357
<i>We're all concerned with human rights,
for God's sake...</i>

42
00:14:23.525 --> 00:14:26.360
<i>...but the kids who want
to get an education have a right too!</i>

43
00:14:31.909 --> 00:14:35.703
<i>Don't you understand? It's against
your own principle, for God's sake!</i>

44
00:14:38.373 --> 00:14:41.542
<i>You can't accomplish anything by
shutting kids off from their...</i>

45
00:14:46.423 --> 00:14:49.967
<i>- if you want... Hold it, hold it!</i>
- Quiet!

46
00:14:50.135 --> 00:14:53.555
<i>If you want to effect any change,
you have to do it within the system.</i>

47
00:14:56.434 --> 00:14:59.144
<i>Okay, cut. That's a wrap.</i>

48
00:15:15.912 --> 00:15:17.371
- I'll walk home tonight.
- Okay.

49
00:15:17.539 --> 00:15:19.998
Here, take that
and drop it at my house, yeah?

50
00:15:20.250 --> 00:15:22.000
- Good night, Tom.
- Good night.

51
00:15:59.540 --> 00:16:02.500
There's not a day in my life
that I don't feel like a fraud.

52
00:16:02.668 --> 00:16:04.988
I mean, priests, doctors, lawyers.
I've talked to them all.

53
00:16:06.422 --> 00:16:08.022
I don't know anyone who hasn't
felt that.

54
00:16:14.138 --> 00:16:15.306
Hello?

55
00:16:15.473 --> 00:16:16.891
In here.

56
00:16:18.643 --> 00:16:20.769
- Hi. How did your day go?
- Oh, not too bad.

57
00:16:20.937 --> 00:16:24.231
It was like the, uh, Walt Disney version
of the Ho Chi Minh story.

58
00:16:24.399 --> 00:16:25.649
Other than that, terrific.

59
00:16:25.817 --> 00:16:28.444
- What we got, anything exciting?
- Here.

60
00:16:28.904 --> 00:16:31.155
- Oh, all right.
- And also, you got an invitation.

61
00:16:31.323 --> 00:16:33.866
- What's this?
- Dinner at the White House.

62
00:16:34.034 --> 00:16:36.285
You're kidding.
Is it a big party or something?

63
00:16:36.453 --> 00:16:37.745
I think it's five or six people.

64
00:16:37.913 --> 00:16:40.748
Oh. Thursday, huh? All right.

65
00:16:40.916 --> 00:16:41.957
Hi, Mom.

66
00:16:42.125 --> 00:16:43.959
What'd you do today?

67
00:16:44.127 --> 00:16:45.794
- Stuff.
- What's that mean, stuff?

68
00:16:45.962 --> 00:16:49.798
Well, uh, me and Sharon played a game
in the backyard.

69
00:16:49.966 --> 00:16:52.301
- You did.
- And we had a picnic down by the river.

70
00:16:52.469 --> 00:16:54.303
That sounds good.

71
00:16:54.471 --> 00:16:55.512
You should have seen.

72
00:16:55.680 --> 00:16:58.683
This man came along on this
beautiful gray horse.

73
00:16:58.851 --> 00:17:00.560
- Really? What kind?
- Wasn't he pretty?

74
00:17:00.728 --> 00:17:02.812
Was it a mare, a gelding, what?

75
00:17:02.980 --> 00:17:05.023
- I think it was a gelding.
- Mm-hm.

76
00:17:05.191 --> 00:17:07.817
It was gray. Oh, it was so beautiful.

77
00:17:07.985 --> 00:17:10.236
The guy let me ride it all around
and everything.

78
00:17:10.404 --> 00:17:12.405
- You're kidding.
- She rode for half an hour.

79
00:17:12.573 --> 00:17:17.494
It was so nice. Oh, I loved it.
Oh, Mom, can't we get a horse?

80
00:17:17.662 --> 00:17:21.039
- Not while we're in Washington, honey.
- Why not, Mom? Ha, ha.

81
00:17:21.207 --> 00:17:23.041
We'll see when we get home, okay?

82
00:17:23.209 --> 00:17:25.835
- When could I have one?
- We'll see, Regan. We'll see.

83
00:17:26.003 --> 00:17:29.214
Hey, listen, on the party invitations,
I wanted to write a personal...

84
00:17:29.382 --> 00:17:32.133
- Regan, don't! Regan, come back here!
- Ha-ha-ha.

85
00:17:36.681 --> 00:17:39.225
- All right, give it up. Give it up!
- No!

86
00:17:39.393 --> 00:17:41.352
- Ooh!
- Ha-ha-ha.

87
00:17:41.520 --> 00:17:43.145
- You'll be sorry! Come on.
- No!

88
00:18:14.094 --> 00:18:15.428
Father?

89
00:18:15.595 --> 00:18:18.055
Could you help an old altar boy?

90
00:18:18.223 --> 00:18:19.266
I'm a Catholic.

91
00:18:42.373 --> 00:18:44.458
All right, come on, man.

92
00:18:45.126 --> 00:18:46.886
- What, are you crazy?
- Go ahead.

93
00:19:45.939 --> 00:19:53.939
Mama?

94
00:20:02.789 --> 00:20:05.874
Dimmy! Dimmy!

95
00:20:09.671 --> 00:20:11.213
Oh, how are you, Mama?

96
00:20:11.381 --> 00:20:13.549
- I'm so glad to see you.
- You look good.

97
00:20:13.716 --> 00:20:15.425
I'm all right.

98
00:20:15.593 --> 00:20:18.053
- How's your leg?
- How about you? You are all right?

99
00:20:18.221 --> 00:20:19.555
I'm fine, Mama. I'm fine.

100
00:20:24.687 --> 00:20:27.814
Your Uncle John passed by to visit me.

101
00:20:27.982 --> 00:20:30.316
- Oh, really? When?
- Last month.

102
00:20:34.905 --> 00:20:37.240
- Too tight?
- No.

103
00:20:38.200 --> 00:20:42.328
You have to stay off it. You can't go up and
down the stairs. You have to give it a rest.

104
00:20:42.496 --> 00:20:43.913
Okay.

105
00:20:54.216 --> 00:20:57.844
I could take you somewhere where
you'd be safe. You wouldn't be alone.

106
00:20:58.012 --> 00:21:01.806
There would be people around. You wouldn't
be sitting here listening to a radio.

107
00:21:06.521 --> 00:21:07.813
You understand me?

108
00:21:07.981 --> 00:21:12.693
This is my house
and I'm not going no place.

109
00:21:25.665 --> 00:21:27.791
Dimmy, you worry for something?

110
00:21:27.959 --> 00:21:29.960
- No, Mama.
- You are not happy?

111
00:21:30.128 --> 00:21:31.879
Tell me, what is the matter?

112
00:21:32.047 --> 00:21:35.216
Mama, I'm all right. I'm fine.
Really, I am.

113
00:22:09.460 --> 00:22:10.919
Here it comes.

114
00:22:11.087 --> 00:22:12.420
There.

115
00:22:15.591 --> 00:22:17.031
- Oh, look at that.
- Do you like it?

116
00:22:17.093 --> 00:22:19.844
Aw, isn't that funny? Ha, ha.

117
00:22:20.471 --> 00:22:23.682
I better put him over here to dry, though.
He's still wet.

118
00:22:23.849 --> 00:22:26.142
Oh, here we go.

119
00:22:26.895 --> 00:22:28.854
There, he can dry there.

120
00:22:29.022 --> 00:22:31.190
Hey, where'd this come from?

121
00:22:32.359 --> 00:22:34.777
- I found it.
- Where?

122
00:22:36.238 --> 00:22:37.530
Closet.

123
00:22:38.699 --> 00:22:40.074
Huh.

124
00:22:40.284 --> 00:22:41.867
You been playing with it?

125
00:22:42.035 --> 00:22:44.036
- Yup.
- Do you know how?

126
00:22:44.204 --> 00:22:46.038
I'll show you.

127
00:22:50.168 --> 00:22:51.711
Wait a minute. You need two.

128
00:22:51.878 --> 00:22:55.172
No, you don't. I do it all the time.

129
00:22:55.340 --> 00:22:57.550
Oh, yeah? Well, let's both play with it.

130
00:23:00.012 --> 00:23:01.887
You really don't want me to play, huh?

131
00:23:02.055 --> 00:23:05.266
No, I do. Captain Howdy said no.

132
00:23:05.434 --> 00:23:08.395
- Captain who?
- Captain Howdy.

133
00:23:08.563 --> 00:23:10.063
Who's Captain Howdy?

134
00:23:10.231 --> 00:23:13.942
You know. I make the questions
and he does the answers.

135
00:23:14.110 --> 00:23:17.779
- Oh, Captain Howdy. Yeah, I see.
- He's nice.

136
00:23:17.947 --> 00:23:19.906
Oh, I'll bet he is.

137
00:23:20.074 --> 00:23:22.909
- Here, I'll show you.
- All right.

138
00:23:23.077 --> 00:23:27.080
Captain Howdy,
do you think my mom's pretty?

139
00:23:29.042 --> 00:23:31.043
Captain Howdy?

140
00:23:31.210 --> 00:23:33.295
Captain Howdy, that isn't very nice.

141
00:23:33.463 --> 00:23:35.964
- Well, maybe he's sleeping.
- You think?

142
00:23:38.009 --> 00:23:40.844
Regan, why are you reading that stuff?

143
00:23:41.012 --> 00:23:42.262
Because I like it.

144
00:23:42.430 --> 00:23:45.182
It's not even a good picture of you.
Look at that.

145
00:23:45.350 --> 00:23:47.934
- You look so mature.
- I wouldn't talk.

146
00:23:48.102 --> 00:23:51.105
You wouldn't talk?
Well, I didn't know they were taking it.

147
00:23:51.273 --> 00:23:53.274
I didn't have my makeup man there.

148
00:23:53.609 --> 00:23:56.110
Let me take an eyelash off your face.

149
00:23:56.278 --> 00:23:58.446
Okay. No, I didn't get it.

150
00:23:58.781 --> 00:24:00.865
- Mm.
- What are we gonna do on your birthday?

151
00:24:01.033 --> 00:24:03.910
Isn't it nice it's on Sunday this year?

152
00:24:04.078 --> 00:24:06.204
No work? What can we do?

153
00:24:06.372 --> 00:24:07.413
I don't know.

154
00:24:07.581 --> 00:24:08.861
Well, what would you like to do?

155
00:24:08.999 --> 00:24:10.917
- Got any ideas?
- Mm-mm.

156
00:24:11.085 --> 00:24:12.752
Hmm?

157
00:24:13.045 --> 00:24:15.755
Let me think. Let me think.
What can we do?

158
00:24:15.923 --> 00:24:18.633
Hey, we never finished seeing
all the sights in Washington.

159
00:24:18.801 --> 00:24:21.135
Didn't get to Lee Mansion
and lots of stuff.

160
00:24:21.303 --> 00:24:24.806
Shall we do that? Go sightseeing?
If it's a nice day?

161
00:24:24.973 --> 00:24:27.100
- Yeah, let's do that.
- Okay.

162
00:24:27.518 --> 00:24:32.689
And tomorrow night,
I'll take you to a movie. Okay?

163
00:24:32.857 --> 00:24:34.775
Oh, I love you.

164
00:24:34.943 --> 00:24:37.486
I love you, Rags.

165
00:24:40.073 --> 00:24:41.198
We'll have a good day, yeah?

166
00:24:41.658 --> 00:24:44.284
You can bring Mr. Dennings, if you like.

167
00:24:44.452 --> 00:24:46.078
Mr. Dennings?

168
00:24:46.246 --> 00:24:48.330
Well, you know, it's okay.

169
00:24:48.498 --> 00:24:49.790
Well, thank you very much...

170
00:24:49.958 --> 00:24:52.960
...but why on earth would I wanna bring
Burke on your birthday?

171
00:24:53.128 --> 00:24:54.670
Well, you like him.

172
00:24:54.838 --> 00:24:58.799
Yeah, I like him. Don't you like him?
Hey, what's going on? What is this?

173
00:24:58.967 --> 00:25:02.469
- You're gonna marry him, aren't you?
- Oh, my God. Are you kidding?

174
00:25:02.637 --> 00:25:04.304
- What?
- Me marry Burke Dennings?

175
00:25:04.472 --> 00:25:06.598
Don't be silly. Of course not.

176
00:25:06.766 --> 00:25:08.684
Where did you ever get an idea like that?

177
00:25:08.852 --> 00:25:10.853
But you like him.

178
00:25:11.020 --> 00:25:14.858
Of course I like him. I like pizzas too,
but I'm not gonna marry one.

179
00:25:15.025 --> 00:25:17.277
You don't like him like Daddy?

180
00:25:18.446 --> 00:25:20.697
Regan, I love your daddy.

181
00:25:20.865 --> 00:25:23.116
I'll always love your daddy, honey.

182
00:25:23.534 --> 00:25:26.870
Okay? Burke just comes
around here a lot, because...

183
00:25:28.497 --> 00:25:30.707
...well, he's lonely.
He don't got nothing to do.

184
00:25:30.875 --> 00:25:33.960
Well, I heard differently.

185
00:25:34.128 --> 00:25:36.463
Oh, you did? What did you hear, huh?

186
00:25:36.630 --> 00:25:39.382
- I don't know. I just thought.
- Come on. What did you hear?

187
00:25:39.550 --> 00:25:41.217
Well, you didn't think so good.

188
00:25:41.385 --> 00:25:43.595
- How do you know? Ha, ha.
- Ha-ha-ha.

189
00:25:43.762 --> 00:25:46.431
Because Burke and I are just friends.
Okay? Really.

190
00:25:46.599 --> 00:25:47.724
Okay.

191
00:25:48.100 --> 00:25:50.143
You ready for sleep?

192
00:25:52.271 --> 00:25:54.982
- Good night.
- Good night, honey.

193
00:26:15.587 --> 00:26:17.630
It's my mother, Tom.

194
00:26:18.089 --> 00:26:20.799
She's alone. I never should have left her.

195
00:26:22.260 --> 00:26:25.262
At least in New York, I'd be near her.
I'd be close to her.

196
00:26:25.430 --> 00:26:28.098
I could see about a transfer, Damien.

197
00:26:29.809 --> 00:26:34.523
I need reassignment, Tom. I want out of
this job. It's wrong, it's no good.

198
00:26:34.690 --> 00:26:36.775
You're the best we've got.

199
00:26:37.652 --> 00:26:39.653
Am I really?

200
00:26:41.989 --> 00:26:44.282
It's more than psychiatry,
and you know that, Tom.

201
00:26:44.450 --> 00:26:47.244
Some of their problems come down
to faith...

202
00:26:47.411 --> 00:26:50.956
...their vocation, the meaning of their
lives, and I can't cut it anymore.

203
00:26:56.128 --> 00:26:58.505
I need out. I'm unfit.

204
00:27:02.593 --> 00:27:04.636
Think I've lost my faith, Tom.

205
00:27:08.140 --> 00:27:09.140
Hello?

206
00:27:09.308 --> 00:27:11.810
Yes, this is Mrs. MacNeil.

207
00:27:12.019 --> 00:27:13.937
Operator, you have got to be kidding!

208
00:27:14.105 --> 00:27:17.066
I have been on this line for 20 minutes!

209
00:27:17.234 --> 00:27:19.527
Jesus Christ. Can you believe this?

210
00:27:19.695 --> 00:27:22.488
He doesn't even call his daughter
on her birthday.

211
00:27:22.656 --> 00:27:24.949
- Maybe the circuit is busy.
- Oh, circuits, my ass!

212
00:27:25.117 --> 00:27:26.492
He doesn't give a shit.

213
00:27:26.660 --> 00:27:30.121
- Why don't you let me...?
- No, I've got it, Sharon. It's all right.

214
00:27:30.289 --> 00:27:33.249
Yes. No, operator,
don't tell me there's no answer.

215
00:27:33.417 --> 00:27:35.209
It's the Hotel Excelsior in Rome.

216
00:27:35.419 --> 00:27:38.004
Would you try it again, please,
and let it ring?

217
00:27:38.171 --> 00:27:40.172
Hello? Yes.

218
00:27:41.174 --> 00:27:45.052
No, operator,
I've given you the number four times.

219
00:27:45.220 --> 00:27:48.598
Do you take an illiteracy test to get
that job, for Christ's sakes?

220
00:27:48.765 --> 00:27:51.142
Don't tell me to be calm, goddamn it!

221
00:28:02.030 --> 00:28:03.322
Yeah?

222
00:28:05.325 --> 00:28:06.617
You're kidding me.

223
00:28:08.620 --> 00:28:11.997
Okay. I thought I just went to bed.

224
00:28:13.333 --> 00:28:14.666
Yeah.

225
00:28:14.834 --> 00:28:17.586
Hey, what are we doing, scene 61?

226
00:28:17.795 --> 00:28:21.757
Okay. Oh, just remind Flo about
that blue belt, huh?

227
00:28:21.924 --> 00:28:23.884
All right. Yeah, I'll see you.

228
00:28:37.023 --> 00:28:38.941
What are you doing here?

229
00:28:39.109 --> 00:28:41.486
My bed was shaking.

230
00:28:41.654 --> 00:28:43.696
I can't get to sleep.

231
00:28:43.864 --> 00:28:45.907
Oh, honey.

232
00:30:06.657 --> 00:30:08.450
Goddamn it.

233
00:30:12.121 --> 00:30:13.580
Jesus.

234
00:30:52.704 --> 00:30:53.746
There's nothing.

235
00:30:53.914 --> 00:30:55.998
Oh, Karl.

236
00:30:56.166 --> 00:30:59.335
Jesus Christ, Karl, don't do that.

237
00:30:59.503 --> 00:31:01.962
Very sorry, but you see, no rats.

238
00:31:02.130 --> 00:31:04.840
No rats. Thanks a lot. That's terrific.

239
00:32:11.743 --> 00:32:14.203
Oh, my God.

240
00:32:31.763 --> 00:32:35.308
Okay. Unroll your fist.

241
