00:53:18.080 --> 00:53:20.081
Chris, doctors.

487
00:53:20.249 --> 00:53:22.333
- This is Dr. Taney.
- Mother, please!

488
00:53:22.501 --> 00:53:24.253
- What is it?
- Please, make it stop!

489
00:53:24.421 --> 00:53:26.714
It's burning! It's burning!

490
00:53:26.882 --> 00:53:29.008
Do something, doctor. Please, help her.

491
00:53:29.176 --> 00:53:34.430
Please, Mother, make it stop!
He's trying to kill me!

492
00:53:34.598 --> 00:53:37.099
Mother! Mother!

493
00:53:41.605 --> 00:53:43.772
All right, Regan,
let's see what the trouble...

494
00:53:43.940 --> 00:53:44.940
Regan!

495
00:53:45.108 --> 00:53:47.359
Keep away! The sow is mine!

496
00:53:48.236 --> 00:53:52.364
Fuck me! Fuck me! Fuck me!

497
00:54:01.958 --> 00:54:04.961
Stay away from me! Stay away!

498
00:54:06.088 --> 00:54:08.590
Hold her steady. Hold her tight!

499
00:54:08.758 --> 00:54:10.467
Don't let them!

500
00:54:34.659 --> 00:54:36.159
She's heavily sedated.

501
00:54:36.869 --> 00:54:39.329
She'll probably sleep through tomorrow.

502
00:54:41.123 --> 00:54:44.793
What was going on in there?
How could she fly off the bed like that?

503
00:54:45.586 --> 00:54:50.716
Pathological states can induce
abnormal strength...

504
00:54:51.176 --> 00:54:53.552
...accelerated motor performance.

505
00:54:54.054 --> 00:54:56.013
For example...

506
00:54:56.265 --> 00:55:00.351
...say a 90-pound woman sees her child
pinned under the wheel of a truck...

507
00:55:00.769 --> 00:55:04.146
...runs out and lifts the wheels
a half a foot up off the ground.

508
00:55:04.314 --> 00:55:06.774
You've heard the story. Same thing here.

509
00:55:08.402 --> 00:55:10.528
Same principle, I mean.

510
00:55:13.198 --> 00:55:14.991
So, what's wrong with her?

511
00:55:16.535 --> 00:55:18.369
We still think that the temporal lobe...

512
00:55:18.537 --> 00:55:21.580
Oh, what are you talking about,
for Christ's sakes?

513
00:55:21.748 --> 00:55:23.791
Did you see her or not?

514
00:55:23.959 --> 00:55:26.168
She's acting like she's fucking
out of her mind!

515
00:55:26.336 --> 00:55:30.716
Psychotic, like a split personality, or...

516
00:55:32.719 --> 00:55:34.636
Oh, Jesus, I'm sorry.

517
00:55:35.013 --> 00:55:37.431
There haven't been more than
100 authentic cases...

518
00:55:37.598 --> 00:55:41.184
...of so-called "split personality,"
Mrs. MacNeil.

519
00:55:42.103 --> 00:55:46.732
Now, I know the temptation is
to leap to psychiatry...

520
00:55:46.899 --> 00:55:51.570
...but any reasonable psychiatrist would
exhaust the somatic possibilities first.

521
00:55:54.532 --> 00:55:56.491
So, what's next?

522
00:55:56.909 --> 00:56:01.079
A pneumoencephalogram,
I would think, to pin down that lesion.

523
00:56:01.247 --> 00:56:03.165
It will involve another spinal.

524
00:56:03.333 --> 00:56:04.666
Oh, Christ!

525
00:56:04.834 --> 00:56:08.296
Well, what we missed in the EEG
and the arteriograms...

526
00:56:08.464 --> 00:56:11.049
...could conceivably turn up there.

527
00:56:11.884 --> 00:56:16.054
At least it would eliminate certain
other possibilities.

528
00:56:29.860 --> 00:56:32.111
Dr. Taney says the x-rays are negative.

529
00:56:33.113 --> 00:56:35.281
In other words, normal.

530
00:56:42.498 --> 00:56:44.040
You keep any drugs in your house?

531
00:56:44.208 --> 00:56:47.627
No, of course not. Nothing like that.

532
00:56:47.795 --> 00:56:49.045
Are you sure?

533
00:56:49.213 --> 00:56:51.465
Well, of course, I'm sure.

534
00:56:51.633 --> 00:56:53.133
I'd tell you.

535
00:56:53.301 --> 00:56:55.386
Christ, I don't even smoke grass.

536
00:57:00.725 --> 00:57:02.810
Are you planning to be home soon?

537
00:57:02.977 --> 00:57:05.062
I mean, uh, to L.A., I mean.

538
00:57:05.480 --> 00:57:07.272
Um...

539
00:57:08.149 --> 00:57:09.650
No, I, uh...

540
00:57:11.152 --> 00:57:13.278
I'm building a new house.

541
00:57:13.988 --> 00:57:16.073
My old one has been sold.

542
00:57:17.242 --> 00:57:18.992
I don't know.

543
00:57:21.162 --> 00:57:23.288
I was gonna take...

544
00:57:25.834 --> 00:57:30.462
I was gonna take Regan to Europe
for a while after she finished school.

545
00:57:32.925 --> 00:57:34.342
Why do you ask?

546
00:57:37.805 --> 00:57:41.057
I think it's time we started looking
for a psychiatrist.

547
00:58:10.129 --> 00:58:11.671
Hello?

548
00:58:26.104 --> 00:58:27.688
Sharon?

549
00:59:04.185 --> 00:59:05.435
Shit.

550
00:59:17.573 --> 00:59:18.782
God.

551
00:59:26.207 --> 00:59:27.707
Sharon!

552
00:59:31.087 --> 00:59:33.129
What do you mean,
leaving Regan by herself?

553
00:59:34.466 --> 00:59:36.226
Her window's wide open.
The room is freezing.

554
00:59:36.385 --> 00:59:38.010
- Didn't he tell you?
- Who?

555
00:59:38.178 --> 00:59:40.179
- Burke is...
- What's Burke got to do with it?

556
00:59:40.347 --> 00:59:42.765
Nobody was here.
When I went to get the Thorazine...

557
00:59:42.933 --> 00:59:45.309
- ...I had him stay with her, and...
- Oh.

558
00:59:45.477 --> 00:59:48.145
- I should have known better. Sorry.
- I guess you should have.

559
00:59:48.313 --> 00:59:49.647
How were the tests?

560
00:59:49.815 --> 00:59:52.149
We have to start looking for a shrink.

561
00:59:52.317 --> 00:59:53.943
Hi, Chuck. Come on in.

562
00:59:55.237 --> 00:59:56.487
I suppose you heard.

563
00:59:56.989 --> 00:59:58.322
Heard what?

564
01:00:00.909 --> 01:00:02.326
You haven't heard.

565
01:00:04.580 --> 01:00:05.621
Burke's dead.

566
01:00:09.209 --> 01:00:12.587
He must have been drunk. He fell from
the top of the steps right outside.

567
01:00:12.754 --> 01:00:15.339
By the time he hit M Street,
he broke his neck.

568
01:00:16.718 --> 01:00:18.010
Oh, God.

569
01:00:19.512 --> 01:00:20.762
No!

570
01:00:27.353 --> 01:00:28.395
Yeah, I know.

571
01:00:43.953 --> 01:00:46.538
Sharon...

572
01:00:46.706 --> 01:00:47.873
Oh, my God.

573
01:00:51.461 --> 01:00:53.670
Oh, my God.

574
01:01:01.805 --> 01:01:05.058
When I touch
your forehead, open your eyes.

575
01:01:12.191 --> 01:01:14.150
Are you comfortable, Regan?

576
01:01:16.904 --> 01:01:18.112
Yes.

577
01:01:19.698 --> 01:01:21.240
How old are you?

578
01:01:21.492 --> 01:01:22.784
Twelve.

579
01:01:24.328 --> 01:01:26.954
Is there someone inside you?

580
01:01:27.539 --> 01:01:29.040
Sometimes.

581
01:01:30.584 --> 01:01:31.834
Who is it?

582
01:01:32.878 --> 01:01:34.253
I don't know.

583
01:01:35.130 --> 01:01:37.173
Is it Captain Howdy?

584
01:01:37.341 --> 01:01:38.676
I don't know.

585
01:01:39.260 --> 01:01:42.846
If I ask him to tell me,
will you let him answer?

586
01:01:43.932 --> 01:01:45.307
No.

587
01:01:46.142 --> 01:01:47.267
Why not?

588
01:01:47.852 --> 01:01:49.812
I'm afraid.

589
01:01:50.105 --> 01:01:52.564
If he talks to me, I think he'll leave you.

590
01:01:52.732 --> 01:01:54.566
Do you want him to leave you?

591
01:01:55.318 --> 01:01:56.402
Yes.

592
01:02:05.245 --> 01:02:08.706
I'm speaking to the person
inside of Regan now.

593
01:02:08.873 --> 01:02:14.086
If you are there, you, too, are hypnotized
and must answer all my questions.

594
01:02:15.714 --> 01:02:17.297
Come forward...

595
01:02:19.300 --> 01:02:21.428
...and answer me now.

596
01:02:30.980 --> 01:02:33.398
Are you the person inside of Regan?

597
01:02:37.653 --> 01:02:39.112
Who are you?

598
01:02:48.622 --> 01:02:50.206
- Help me!
- Let go!

599
01:03:36.838 --> 01:03:38.714
Father Karras?

600
01:03:41.927 --> 01:03:43.470
Have we met?

601
01:03:44.639 --> 01:03:48.391
No, we haven't met,
but they said I could tell.

602
01:03:48.559 --> 01:03:51.061
That you look like a boxer.

603
01:03:51.771 --> 01:03:54.481
William F. Kinderman. Homicide.

604
01:03:55.066 --> 01:03:56.650
What's this all about?

605
01:03:56.818 --> 01:04:00.028
It's true. You do look like a boxer.

606
01:04:00.279 --> 01:04:03.323
Like John Garfield in Body and Soul.

607
01:04:03.491 --> 01:04:06.201
Exactly. John Garfield.
People tell you that, Father?

608
01:04:08.204 --> 01:04:10.247
Do people tell you
you look like Paul Newman?

609
01:04:10.414 --> 01:04:11.873
Always.

610
01:04:18.464 --> 01:04:21.842
Well, you know this director
who was doing the film here...

611
01:04:22.009 --> 01:04:23.511
...Burke Dennings?

612
01:04:23.679 --> 01:04:25.179
I've seen him.

613
01:04:25.347 --> 01:04:26.848
You've seen him.

614
01:04:27.683 --> 01:04:31.227
You're also familiar how last week
he died?

615
01:04:31.395 --> 01:04:33.104
Only what I read in the papers.

616
01:04:33.272 --> 01:04:37.942
Father, what do you know on
the subject of witchcraft?

617
01:04:38.485 --> 01:04:41.445
From the witching end, not the hunting.

618
01:04:41.613 --> 01:04:43.447
I once did a paper on it.

619
01:04:43.615 --> 01:04:44.824
Really?

620
01:04:44.992 --> 01:04:47.076
From the psychiatric end.

621
01:04:47.870 --> 01:04:49.745
I know. I read it.

622
01:04:51.290 --> 01:04:54.083
All of this desecration in the church...

623
01:04:54.251 --> 01:04:57.587
...do you think this has anything to do
with witchcraft?

624
01:04:58.297 --> 01:05:01.299
Maybe. Some rituals used in
the black mass, maybe.

625
01:05:01.466 --> 01:05:05.971
And now Dennings.
You read how he died?

626
01:05:06.139 --> 01:05:07.472
In a fall.

627
01:05:10.727 --> 01:05:15.480
Let me tell you how.
And please, Father...

628
01:05:15.982 --> 01:05:17.691
...confidential.

629
01:05:19.193 --> 01:05:21.403
Burke Dennings, good Father...

630
01:05:21.571 --> 01:05:24.489
...was found at the bottom of those steps
leading to M Street...

631
01:05:24.657 --> 01:05:27.576
...with his head turned completely
around...

632
01:05:27.744 --> 01:05:29.703
...facing backwards.

633
01:05:35.335 --> 01:05:36.501
Didn't happen in the fall?

634
01:05:37.170 --> 01:05:38.754
It's possible.

635
01:05:40.548 --> 01:05:43.508
- Possible, however...
- Unlikely.

636
01:05:43.676 --> 01:05:45.135
Exactly.

637
01:05:46.555 --> 01:05:50.683
So on the one hand,
we've got a witchcraft kind of murder...

638
01:05:50.851 --> 01:05:56.314
...and on the other hand, a black mass-type
desecration in the church.

639
01:05:56.482 --> 01:05:59.692
You think the killer
and the desecrator are the same?

640
01:06:01.195 --> 01:06:02.737
Maybe somebody crazy...

641
01:06:02.905 --> 01:06:05.907
...somebody with a spite against
the Church.

642
01:06:06.075 --> 01:06:08.868
Some unconscious rebellion.

643
01:06:09.036 --> 01:06:10.370
A sick priest, is that it?

644
01:06:10.537 --> 01:06:15.208
Look, Father, this is hard for you.
Please, I understand...

645
01:06:15.376 --> 01:06:18.753
...but for priests on the campus here,
you're the psychiatrist.

646
01:06:18.921 --> 01:06:21.339
You'd know who was sick at the time,
who wasn't.

647
01:06:21.507 --> 01:06:24.300
I mean, this kind of sickness,
you'd know that.

648
01:06:24.468 --> 01:06:27.346
I don't know anyone who fits
that description.

649
01:06:28.890 --> 01:06:30.391
Ah.

650
01:06:32.060 --> 01:06:34.645
Doctor's ethics.
If you knew, you wouldn't tell, huh?

651
01:06:34.813 --> 01:06:35.980
No, I probably wouldn't.

652
01:06:36.606 --> 01:06:39.525
Not to bother you with trivia,
but a psychiatrist...

653
01:06:39.693 --> 01:06:42.528
...in sunny California, no less...

654
01:06:42.696 --> 01:06:47.157
...was put in jail for not telling the
police what he knew about a patient.

655
01:06:47.826 --> 01:06:52.121
- Is that a threat?
- No, I mention it only in passing.

656
01:06:53.748 --> 01:06:55.833
Incidentally,
I mention it only in passing...

657
01:06:56.001 --> 01:06:59.086
...I could always tell the judge it was
a matter of confession.

658
01:07:02.924 --> 01:07:05.175
Hey, Father, wait a minute.

659
01:07:05.343 --> 01:07:07.261
- Do you like movies?
- Very much.

660
01:07:07.429 --> 01:07:10.473
Well, I get passes
to the best shows in town.

661
01:07:10.641 --> 01:07:14.602
Mrs. K, though, you know,
she gets tired, never likes to go.

662
01:07:14.770 --> 01:07:16.896
- That's too bad.
- Yeah, I hate to go alone.

663
01:07:17.064 --> 01:07:19.566
I love to talk film...

664
01:07:19.734 --> 01:07:23.153
...discuss, to critique.

665
01:07:23.320 --> 01:07:28.491
You want to see a film with me?
I got passes to the Crest. It's Othello.

666
01:07:28.659 --> 01:07:30.493
- Who's in it?
- Who's in it?

667
01:07:30.661 --> 01:07:34.622
Debbie Reynolds, Desdemona,
and Othello, Groucho Marx. You happy?

668
01:07:34.790 --> 01:07:36.791
- I've seen it.
- Ah.

669
01:07:37.126 --> 01:07:40.837
One last time. You can think
of some priest who fits the bill?

670
01:07:41.005 --> 01:07:45.300
- Come on.
- No, answer the question, Father Paranoia.

671
01:07:46.469 --> 01:07:49.137
All right. All right.

672
01:07:50.098 --> 01:07:52.641
- You know who I think really did it?
- Who?

673
01:07:52.809 --> 01:07:54.643
The Dominicans. Go pick on them.

674
01:07:55.395 --> 01:07:57.897
I could have you deported,
you know that?

675
01:08:00.025 --> 01:08:01.233
I lied.

676
01:08:02.652 --> 01:08:04.487
You look like Sal Mineo.

677
01:08:08.825 --> 01:08:12.244
It looks like a type of disorder
that's, uh, rarely ever seen anymore...

678
01:08:12.412 --> 01:08:14.497
...except in primitive cultures.

679
01:08:14.873 --> 01:08:19.001
We call it, uh,
somnambular-form possession.

680
01:08:19.628 --> 01:08:22.338
Quite frankly, we really don't know
much about it at all...

681
01:08:22.506 --> 01:08:26.842
...except that it starts with a conflict
or a guilt...

682
01:08:27.010 --> 01:08:30.805
...and it leads to the patient's delusions
that his body has been invaded...

683
01:08:30.973 --> 01:08:34.810
...by some alien intelligence. Um...

684
01:08:34.977 --> 01:08:36.144
A spirit, if you will.

685
01:08:36.312 --> 01:08:39.815
Look, I'm telling you again,
and you'd better believe me...

686
01:08:39.982 --> 01:08:42.818
...I am not going to lock her up
in some goddamn asylum.

687
01:08:42.985 --> 01:08:45.654
- Well, it's out of...
- And I don't care what you call it.

688
01:08:45.822 --> 01:08:47.531
I'm not putting her away.

689
01:08:47.698 --> 01:08:49.199
Well, I'm sorry.

690
01:08:49.367 --> 01:08:51.201
You're sorry? Jesus Christ!

691
01:08:51.369 --> 01:08:56.081
Eighty-eight doctors, and all you can
tell me with all your bullshit is...

692
01:09:12.933 --> 01:09:17.728
Of course, there is one outside chance
for a cure.

693
01:09:18.522 --> 01:09:24.360
But, um, I think of it
as a shock treatment.

694
01:09:25.362 --> 01:09:27.321
As I said, it's a very outside chance...

695
01:09:27.489 --> 01:09:30.158
Would you just name it, for God's sakes?
What is it?

696
01:09:30.325 --> 01:09:32.827
- Do you have any religious beliefs?
- No.

697
01:09:32.995 --> 01:09:35.413
What about your daughter?

698
01:09:35.581 --> 01:09:37.373
No. Why?

699
01:09:37.583 --> 01:09:39.250
Have you ever heard of exorcism?

700
01:09:41.712 --> 01:09:44.422
Well, it's a stylized ritual...

701
01:09:44.590 --> 01:09:51.179
...in which the, uh, rabbi or the priest try
to drive out the so-called invading spirit.

702
01:09:51.346 --> 01:09:53.432
It's been pretty much discarded
these days...

703
01:09:53.600 --> 01:09:58.353
...except by the Catholics, who keep it
in the closet as a sort of embarrassment.

704
01:09:58.563 --> 01:10:01.607
But it, uh, has worked, in fact...

705
01:10:01.774 --> 01:10:04.693
...although not for the reasons they think,
of course.

706
01:10:04.861 --> 01:10:08.614
It's purely force of suggestion.

707
01:10:08.781 --> 01:10:13.577
The, uh... The victim's belief in
possession is what helped cause it...

708
01:10:13.745 --> 01:10:15.370
...so in that same way...

709
01:10:15.538 --> 01:10:18.790
...the belief in the power of exorcism
can make it disappear.

710
01:10:21.169 --> 01:10:25.214
You're telling me that I should
take my daughter to a witch doctor.

711
01:10:26.132 --> 01:10:27.591
Is that it?

712
01:12:06.319 --> 01:12:07.944
Karl?

713
01:12:09.238 --> 01:12:11.740
Did you put this in Regan's bedroom?

714
01:12:14.452 --> 01:12:16.411
She's going to be well?

715
01:12:17.621 --> 01:12:22.042
Karl, if you put this in Regan's bedroom,
I want you to tell me. Now, did you?

716
01:12:22.209 --> 01:12:24.878
No, not me.

717
01:12:25.046 --> 01:12:26.087
I didn't.

718
01:12:44.274 --> 01:12:47.610
This was under Regan's pillow.
Did you put it there?

719
01:12:47.986 --> 01:12:49.403
Of course, I didn't.

720
01:12:50.989 --> 01:12:52.198
I didn't put it.

721
01:12:53.992 --> 01:12:56.410
- Excuse me, madam.
- What?

722
01:12:57.454 --> 01:12:59.622
- A man to see you.
- What man?

723
01:13:06.213 --> 01:13:08.589
Might your daughter remember, perhaps...

724
01:13:08.757 --> 01:13:11.759
...if Mr. Dennings was in her room
that night?

725
01:13:13.220 --> 01:13:15.137
- Why do you ask?
- Mm.

726
01:13:15.555 --> 01:13:17.390
Might she remember?

727
01:13:19.559 --> 01:13:22.854
No, she was heavily sedated.

728
01:13:23.356 --> 01:13:24.815
It's serious?

729
01:13:25.650 --> 01:13:27.275
Yes, I'm afraid it is.

730
01:13:28.736 --> 01:13:31.196
- May I ask...?
- We still don't know.

731
01:13:32.156 --> 01:13:33.740
Watch out for drafts.

732
01:13:33.908 --> 01:13:39.329
A draft in the fall when the house is hot
is a magic carpet for bacteria.

733
01:13:39.497 --> 01:13:41.289
Excuse me, madam. Anything else?

734
01:13:41.457 --> 01:13:43.583
No, Karl, we're fine. Thank you.

735
01:13:44.168 --> 01:13:45.961
It's all right, Karl.

736
01:13:50.174 --> 01:13:51.800
Why are you asking all this?

737
01:13:51.968 --> 01:13:53.343
It's strange.

738
01:13:54.595 --> 01:13:59.015
The deceased comes to visit,
stays only 20 minutes...

739
01:13:59.183 --> 01:14:03.354
...and leaves all alone a very sick girl.

740
01:14:04.815 --> 01:14:06.607
And speaking plainly, Mrs. MacNeil...

741
01:14:06.775 --> 01:14:11.904
...it isn't likely he would fall
from a window.

742
01:14:12.531 --> 01:14:15.450
Besides, a fall wouldn't do to his neck
what we found.

743
01:14:15.617 --> 01:14:18.453
Except maybe one chance in a thousand.

744
01:14:18.996 --> 01:14:21.247
No. My hunch...

745
01:14:21.540 --> 01:14:24.792
My opinion...

746
01:14:24.960 --> 01:14:28.963
...he was killed by a very powerful man:
point one.

747
01:14:30.299 --> 01:14:32.800
And the fracturing of
his skull: point two...

748
01:14:32.968 --> 01:14:35.720
...plus the various other things
we mentioned...

749
01:14:36.972 --> 01:14:39.849
...would make it very probable...

750
01:14:40.017 --> 01:14:42.811
...probable, not certain...

751
01:14:43.438 --> 01:14:49.234
...that the deceased was killed and
then pushed from your daughter's window.

752
01:14:49.402 --> 01:14:53.989
But nobody was in the room
except your daughter, so how can this be?

753
01:14:57.827 --> 01:15:00.162
It could be one way.

754
01:15:00.538 --> 01:15:03.457
If someone came calling
between the time Miss Spencer left...

755
01:15:03.625 --> 01:15:05.792
...and the time you returned.

756
01:15:05.960 --> 01:15:08.462
Judas Priest, just a second.

757
01:15:09.464 --> 01:15:12.549
- The servants? They have visitors?
- Not at all.

758
01:15:12.717 --> 01:15:15.260
You were expecting a package that day,
some delivery?

759
01:15:15.428 --> 01:15:16.637
Not that I know of.

760
01:15:16.804 --> 01:15:19.473
Groceries, cleaning, uh, a package?

761
01:15:19.641 --> 01:15:22.351
I really wouldn't know.
See, Karl takes care of all that.

762
01:15:24.438 --> 01:15:25.730
I see.

763
01:15:25.898 --> 01:15:27.857
Would you like to ask him?

764
01:15:28.734 --> 01:15:31.194
No, never mind, it's...

765
01:15:32.530 --> 01:15:34.864
It's very remote.

766
01:15:35.574 --> 01:15:38.117
No, never mind.

767
01:15:38.619 --> 01:15:40.161
Yeah.

768
01:15:48.671 --> 01:15:50.630
Would you like some more coffee?

769
01:15:51.298 --> 01:15:52.966
Please.

770
01:16:27.919 --> 01:16:29.336
That's cute.

771
01:16:30.589 --> 01:16:32.840
Your daughter, she's the artist?

772
01:16:35.135 --> 01:16:37.177
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

773
01:16:37.846 --> 01:16:39.680
Incidentally, um...

774
01:16:40.724 --> 01:16:42.516
...you might ask your daughter...

775
01:16:42.684 --> 01:16:46.021
...if she remembers seeing Mr. Dennings
in her room that night.

776
01:16:46.188 --> 01:16:49.524
Look, he wouldn't have any reason
in the world to go up to her room.

777
01:16:49.692 --> 01:16:52.777
Oh, I know, I realize...

778
01:16:53.112 --> 01:16:56.448
...but if certain British doctors never
asked, "What is this fungus?"...

779
01:16:56.616 --> 01:16:59.826
...we wouldn't today have penicillin.
Correct?

780
01:17:00.077 --> 01:17:03.663
Well, when she's better, I'll ask her.

781
01:17:03.831 --> 01:17:06.458
- Yeah, couldn't hurt.
- Okay.

782
01:17:06.626 --> 01:17:09.044
Uh, in the meantime...

783
01:17:10.546 --> 01:17:11.880
That's okay.

784
01:17:12.048 --> 01:17:16.217
- I really hate to ask you this, but...
- What?

785
01:17:16.719 --> 01:17:20.555
For my daughter,
could you please give an autograph?

786
01:17:20.723 --> 01:17:23.099
Of course. Uh, where's a pencil?

787
01:17:23.267 --> 01:17:25.101
Right here. Here.

788
01:17:25.686 --> 01:17:26.978
Oh.

789
01:17:27.356 --> 01:17:28.564
She'd love it.

790
01:17:30.192 --> 01:17:31.734
And what's her name?

791
01:17:34.279 --> 01:17:36.530
I lied. it's for me.

792
01:17:38.325 --> 01:17:42.370
- The spelling is on the back: Kinderman.
- Okay.

793
01:17:42.788 --> 01:17:45.956
You know that film you made, um, Angel?

794
01:17:46.124 --> 01:17:48.542
- Oh, yeah.
- I saw that six times.

795
01:17:48.710 --> 01:17:50.920
- Really?
- It was beautiful.

796
01:17:51.338 --> 01:17:53.881
Ha, ha. Thank you.

797
01:17:56.551 --> 01:17:59.720
You're a very nice lady.

798
01:18:01.973 --> 01:18:04.308
- Thank you.
- You're a nice man.

799
01:18:05.268 --> 01:18:08.479
Uh, I'll come back
when she's feeling better.

800
01:18:12.276 --> 01:18:14.111
- Bye.
- Bye.

801
01:18:34.966 --> 01:18:36.925
Please, no!

802
01:18:37.093 --> 01:18:39.177
- Do it!
- Please, don't!

803
01:18:39.345 --> 01:18:42.723
<i>You bitch! Do it! Do it!</i>

804
01:18:42.890 --> 01:18:44.474
Please, no!

805
01:18:46.978 --> 01:18:50.064
<i>Yes! Let Jesus fuck you!</i>

806
01:18:50.232 --> 01:18:53.151
<i>Let Jesus fuck you! Let him fuck you!</i>

807
01:18:57.448 --> 01:18:58.489
Aah!

808
01:18:58.657 --> 01:19:01.492
Give it! Give it to me! Aah!

809
01:19:02.202 --> 01:19:05.663
- Ugh!
<i>- Lick me! Lick me!</i>

810
01:19:11.170 --> 01:19:12.253
Chris!

811
01:19:13.881 --> 01:19:16.966
Mrs. MacNeil, open the door!

812
01:19:24.266 --> 01:19:25.516
Open the door!

813
01:19:25.684 --> 01:19:28.144
<i>Do you know what she did...</i>

814
01:19:28.312 --> 01:19:30.354
<i>...your cunting daughter?</i>

815
01:19:50.376 --> 01:19:52.002
Chris MacNeil?

816
01:19:52.337 --> 01:19:53.378
Please, go away.

817
01:19:53.546 --> 01:19:55.631
I'm Father Karras.

818
01:19:57.550 --> 01:19:59.426
I'm very sorry. Hello.

819
01:19:59.594 --> 01:20:01.929
I should have told you
I wouldn't be in uniform.

820
01:20:02.096 --> 01:20:03.680
Yeah, that would have helped.

821
01:20:03.848 --> 01:20:06.225
- Have you got a cigarette, Father?
- Sure.

822
01:20:10.230 --> 01:20:11.396
Thanks.

823
01:20:23.577 --> 01:20:24.911
Cold.

824
01:20:25.079 --> 01:20:26.246
Yeah.

825
01:20:28.123 --> 01:20:29.582
Uh...

826
01:20:30.751 --> 01:20:33.211
How did a shrink ever get to be a priest?

827
01:20:33.379 --> 01:20:36.339
It's the other way around. The Society
sent me through medical school.

828
01:20:36.507 --> 01:20:37.632
Oh.

829
01:20:37.800 --> 01:20:39.133
Where?

830
01:20:40.052 --> 01:20:43.555
Harvard, Bellevue, Johns Hopkins.

831
01:20:43.722 --> 01:20:46.099
- Places like that.
- I see.

832
01:20:47.977 --> 01:20:50.937
- You're a friend of Father Dyer's, right?
- Yes, I am.

833
01:20:51.105 --> 01:20:53.481
- Pretty close?
- Pretty close.

834
01:20:53.650 --> 01:20:55.526
Did he talk to you about my party?

835
01:20:55.694 --> 01:20:57.278
He sure did.

836
01:20:57.821 --> 01:20:59.363
About my daughter?

837
01:20:59.531 --> 01:21:01.323
No, I didn't know you had one.

838
01:21:03.618 --> 01:21:06.161
- He didn't mention her?
- No.

839
01:21:06.329 --> 01:21:07.955
Oh.

840
01:21:08.415 --> 01:21:10.624
Didn't tell you what she did?

841
01:21:10.792 --> 01:21:12.668
He didn't mention her.

842
01:21:14.296 --> 01:21:16.714
Priests are pretty tight-mouthed,
then, huh?

843
01:21:16.882 --> 01:21:18.883
That depends.

844
01:21:19.175 --> 01:21:21.176
- On what?
- The priest.

845
01:21:21.970 --> 01:21:23.429
Sure.

846
01:21:24.931 --> 01:21:28.559
I mean, what if a person,
uh, came to you...

847
01:21:28.727 --> 01:21:31.979
...you know, that was a murderer
or criminal of some kind...

848
01:21:32.147 --> 01:21:35.400
...and they wanted some kind of help?

849
01:21:35.568 --> 01:21:37.569
I mean, would you have to turn him in?

850
01:21:37.737 --> 01:21:40.780
Well, if he came to me for
spiritual advice, I'd say no.

851
01:21:40.948 --> 01:21:42.908
- You wouldn't?
- No, I wouldn't.

852
01:21:43.451 --> 01:21:45.535
But I would try to convince him
to turn himself in.

853
01:21:45.703 --> 01:21:47.162
Mm-hm.

854
01:21:47.538 --> 01:21:51.625
And, uh, how do you go about
getting an exorcism?

855
01:21:55.880 --> 01:21:57.380
I beg your pardon?

856
01:22:00.843 --> 01:22:06.389
If, um... If a person's, you know,
possessed by a demon, or something...

857
01:22:06.557 --> 01:22:08.975
...how do they get an exorcism?

858
01:22:09.685 --> 01:22:13.647
I'd have to get them into a time machine
and get them back to the 16th century.

859
01:22:13.814 --> 01:22:15.482
I didn't get you.

860
01:22:15.650 --> 01:22:17.860
It just doesn't happen anymore,
Mrs. MacNeil.

861
01:22:18.028 --> 01:22:19.737
Oh, yeah? Since when?

862
01:22:21.031 --> 01:22:24.992
Well, since we learned about mental
illness, paranoia, schizophrenia.

863
01:22:25.160 --> 01:22:27.119
All those things they taught me
at Harvard.

864
01:22:27.287 --> 01:22:29.956
Mrs. MacNeil,
since the day I joined the Jesuits...

865
01:22:30.123 --> 01:22:33.876
...I've never met one priest
who has performed an exorcism. Not one.

866
01:22:35.295 --> 01:22:37.171
Yeah, well...

867
01:22:39.633 --> 01:22:43.427
...it just so happens that somebody
very close to me...

868
01:22:43.887 --> 01:22:45.554
...is probably possessed.

869
01:22:46.556 --> 01:22:48.265
And needs an exorcist.

870
01:22:48.725 --> 01:22:51.560
Father Karras, it's my little girl.

871
01:22:53.105 --> 01:22:55.356
Then that's all the more reason
to forget about exorcism.

872
01:22:55.524 --> 01:22:56.774
Why? I don't understand.

873
01:22:56.942 --> 01:22:59.653
- To begin with, it could make things worse.
- Oh, how?

874
01:22:59.821 --> 01:23:02.072
Secondly, the Church,
before it approves an exorcism...

875
01:23:02.240 --> 01:23:05.450
...conducts an investigation to see if
it's warranted. That takes time.

876
01:23:05.618 --> 01:23:07.258
- Yeah, but...
- Meanwhile, your daughter...

877
01:23:07.328 --> 01:23:10.038
- You could do it yourself.
- No. I'd need Church approval...

878
01:23:10.206 --> 01:23:13.041
- ...and that's rarely given.
- But... Uh...

879
01:23:15.086 --> 01:23:16.670
- Could you see her?
- Yes, I could.

880
01:23:16.838 --> 01:23:18.558
I could see her as a psychiatrist, but l...

881
01:23:18.715 --> 01:23:21.049
Oh, not a psychiatrist. She needs a priest.

882
01:23:21.217 --> 01:23:24.886
She's seen every fucking psychiatrist
in the world, and they sent me to you.

883
01:23:25.054 --> 01:23:26.805
Now are you gonna send me
back to them?

884
01:23:26.973 --> 01:23:29.850
- Jesus Christ, won't somebody help me?
- You don't understand...

885
01:23:30.018 --> 01:23:33.103
Oh, God, can't you help her?
Just help her!

886
01:24:04.136 --> 01:24:05.887
It wants no straps.

887
01:24:21.529 --> 01:24:22.863
Hello, Regan.

888
01:24:26.451 --> 01:24:29.286
I'm a friend of your mother's.
I'd like to help you.

889
01:24:29.996 --> 01:24:32.372
You might loosen these straps, then.

890
01:24:33.333 --> 01:24:35.667
I'm afraid you might hurt yourself,
Regan.

891
01:24:36.377 --> 01:24:38.504
<i>I'm not Regan.</i>

892
01:24:39.339 --> 01:24:40.631
I see.

893
01:24:45.553 --> 01:24:48.472
Well, then, let's introduce ourselves.
I'm Damien Karras.

894
01:24:48.681 --> 01:24:50.265
<i>And I'm the devil.</i>

895
01:24:50.433 --> 01:24:52.351
<i>Now, kindly undo these straps.</i>

896
01:24:53.019 --> 01:24:55.604
If you're the devil,
why not make the straps disappear?

897
01:24:55.772 --> 01:24:58.941
<i>That's much too vulgar a display
of power, Karras.</i>

898
01:25:00.401 --> 01:25:01.736
Where's Regan?

899
01:25:02.029 --> 01:25:03.863
<i>In here, with us.</i>

900
01:25:06.075 --> 01:25:08.326
Show me Regan
and I'll loosen one of the straps.

901
01:25:09.245 --> 01:25:12.122
<i>Could you help an old altar boy, Father?</i>

902
01:25:13.082 --> 01:25:15.458
<i>Your mother's in here with us, Karras.</i>

903
01:25:15.626 --> 01:25:17.710
<i>Would you like to leave a message?</i>

904
01:25:17.878 --> 01:25:20.130
I'll see that she gets it.

905
01:25:25.511 --> 01:25:27.053
If that's true...

906
01:25:29.598 --> 01:25:32.475
...then you must know my mother's
maiden name.

907
01:25:34.061 --> 01:25:42.061
What is it?

908
01:26:38.961 --> 01:26:40.462
Thank you.

909
01:26:42.965 --> 01:26:47.802
Look, I'm only against the possibility of
doing your daughter more harm than good.

910
01:26:48.221 --> 01:26:51.306
Nothing you could do
could make it any worse.

911
01:26:51.849 --> 01:26:53.516
I can't do it.

912
01:26:54.143 --> 01:26:56.269
I need evidence that the Church
would accept...

913
01:26:56.437 --> 01:26:58.313
- ...as signs of possession.
- Like what?

914
01:26:58.481 --> 01:27:00.899
Speaking in a language
she's never known or studied.

915
01:27:01.067 --> 01:27:02.400
What else?

916
01:27:03.653 --> 01:27:06.989
I don't know. I'd have to look it up.

917
01:27:07.157 --> 01:27:09.533
I thought you were supposed
to be an expert.

918
01:27:10.410 --> 01:27:12.328
There are no experts.

919
01:27:13.163 --> 01:27:16.624
You probably know as much about
possession as most priests.

920
01:27:17.209 --> 01:27:19.502
Look, your daughter doesn't say
she's a demon.

921
01:27:19.670 --> 01:27:22.046
She says she's the devil himself.

922
01:27:22.214 --> 01:27:24.340
If you've seen as many psychotics
as I have...

923
01:27:24.508 --> 01:27:28.177
...you'd realize that's the same thing
as saying you're Napoleon Bonaparte.

924
01:27:29.388 --> 01:27:33.975
You asked me what I think is best
for your daughter.

925
01:27:34.851 --> 01:27:40.606
Six months under observation
in the best hospital you can find.

926
01:27:43.235 --> 01:27:45.319
You show me Regan's double...

927
01:27:45.487 --> 01:27:49.574
...same face, same voice, everything...

928
01:27:49.742 --> 01:27:51.785
...and I'd know it wasn't Regan.

929
01:27:52.704 --> 01:27:54.288
I'd know in my gut.

930
01:27:55.707 --> 01:27:59.293
I'm telling you that that thing upstairs
isn't my daughter.

931
01:28:00.003 --> 01:28:02.421
I want you to tell me that you know
for a fact...

932
01:28:02.588 --> 01:28:05.674
...that there's nothing wrong
with my daughter except in her mind.

933
01:28:05.842 --> 01:28:08.885
Tell me you know for a fact
that an exorcism wouldn't do any good.

934
01:28:09.053 --> 01:28:11.013
You tell me that!

935
01:28:22.567 --> 01:28:25.444
Did Regan know a priest was
coming over?

936
01:28:26.904 --> 01:28:30.033
- No.
- Did you know my mother died recently?

937
01:28:30.743 --> 01:28:33.244
- Yes, I did. I'm very sorry.
- No.

938
01:28:33.912 --> 01:28:35.580
Is Regan aware of it?

939
01:28:36.957 --> 01:28:38.249
Not at all.

940
01:28:39.752 --> 01:28:41.085
Why do you ask?

941
01:28:42.921 --> 01:28:44.922
It's not important. Good night.

942
01:29:11.576 --> 01:29:13.577
Hello?

943
01:29:15.955 --> 01:29:20.250
- Here, take it and just don't...
- Okay. Um.

944
01:29:20.418 --> 01:29:21.877
<i>Hello, Daddy?</i>

945
01:29:22.045 --> 01:29:23.629
<i>This is me.</i>

946
01:29:24.422 --> 01:29:27.549
<i>- What should I say? I don't know.
- Just talk to your daddy.</i>

947
01:29:27.717 --> 01:29:30.052
<i>- Anything you want.
- All right, um...</i>

948
01:29:30.220 --> 01:29:34.932
<i>Tell him what you've been doing
and how you're feeling and like that.</i>

949
01:29:36.434 --> 01:29:37.684
<i>Uh...</i>

950
01:29:37.852 --> 01:29:40.312
<i>Well, you see, um...</i>

951
01:29:40.730 --> 01:29:43.816
<i>I mean, I hope you can hear me.
Can you hear me okay?</i>

952
01:29:43.983 --> 01:29:46.183
<i>- Well, uh, let me see.
- He's not gonna answer you.</i>

953
01:29:46.319 --> 01:29:48.404
<i>Uh, ha-ha-ha.</i>

954
01:29:48.571 --> 01:29:50.907
<i>- Go on. Talk to your daddy, honey.
- Um...</i>

955
01:29:51.075 --> 01:29:53.410
<i>I don't know what to say, though. Um...</i>

956
01:29:53.869 --> 01:29:57.163
<i>Well, let's see. First we... No.</i>

957
01:29:57.540 --> 01:30:00.667
<i>- Wait. I don't know.
- Come on, Regan.</i>

958
01:30:00.835 --> 01:30:02.836
<i>- Tell him about Washington.
- Okay.</i>

959
01:30:03.003 --> 01:30:05.839
<i>See, we're in Washington now,
Daddy, and...</i>

960
01:30:08.134 --> 01:30:11.719
He broke the bread,
gave it to his disciples and said:

961
01:30:14.515 --> 01:30:17.058
"Take this, all of you, and eat it..."

962
01:30:20.896 --> 01:30:22.188
"...for this is my body."

963
01:30:28.904 --> 01:30:31.824
When the supper was ended,
he took the cup.

964
01:30:32.284 --> 01:30:35.244
Again he gave you thanks and praise.

965
01:30:35.871 --> 01:30:39.248
He gave the cup to his disciples and said,
"Take this..."

966
01:30:39.583 --> 01:30:41.959
"...all of you, and drink from it."

967
01:30:45.338 --> 01:30:47.923
"This is the cup of my blood."

968
01:30:49.426 --> 01:30:53.512
"The blood of the new and everlasting
covenant, the mystery of faith."

969
01:30:54.806 --> 01:30:57.224
<i>What an excellent day for an exorcism.</i>

970
01:30:59.394 --> 01:31:00.603
You'd like that?

971
01:31:00.770 --> 01:31:02.688
<i>Intensely.</i>

972
01:31:03.565 --> 01:31:05.941
But wouldn't that drive you
out of Regan?

973
01:31:06.109 --> 01:31:08.360
<i>It would bring us together.</i>

974
01:31:09.738 --> 01:31:10.946
You and Regan?

975
01:31:11.114 --> 01:31:12.824
<i>You and us.</i>

976
01:31:24.086 --> 01:31:28.006
- Did you do that?
- Uh-huh.

977
01:31:32.929 --> 01:31:34.930
- Do it again.
<i>- In time.</i>

978
01:31:35.097 --> 01:31:36.681
No, now.

979
01:31:36.849 --> 01:31:38.600
<i>In time.</i>

