01:53:22.185 --> 01:53:24.979
Let's rest before we start again.

1222
01:54:00.224 --> 01:54:03.977
Why this girl? It doesn't make sense.

1223
01:54:12.486 --> 01:54:15.614
I think the point is to make us despair.

1224
01:54:18.659 --> 01:54:20.827
To see ourselves as...

1225
01:54:22.330 --> 01:54:24.581
...animal and ugly.

1226
01:54:27.919 --> 01:54:31.922
To reject the possibility that God
could love us.

1227
01:54:39.473 --> 01:54:41.807
Will you excuse me, Damien?

1228
01:55:33.736 --> 01:55:38.073
Why? Why?

1229
01:55:39.742 --> 01:55:43.704
No. No.

1230
01:56:09.440 --> 01:56:12.817
<i>Dimmy, why you do this to me?</i>

1231
01:56:15.279 --> 01:56:18.740
<i>Please, Dimmy. I'm afraid.</i>

1232
01:56:20.284 --> 01:56:22.368
You're not my mother.

1233
01:56:23.328 --> 01:56:25.538
<i>Dimmy, please!</i>

1234
01:56:38.635 --> 01:56:40.304
What is it?

1235
01:56:45.351 --> 01:56:46.435
Her heart.

1236
01:56:46.978 --> 01:56:48.854
Can you give her something?

1237
01:56:49.022 --> 01:56:50.856
She'll go into a coma.

1238
01:56:54.819 --> 01:56:56.987
You're not my mother!

1239
01:56:57.155 --> 01:56:58.155
Don't listen.

1240
01:56:58.323 --> 01:56:59.948
<i>Why, Dimmy?</i>

1241
01:57:00.909 --> 01:57:02.242
Damien.

1242
01:57:02.410 --> 01:57:03.660
<i>- Dimmy, please.</i>
- Damien.

1243
01:57:08.083 --> 01:57:09.833
Get out.

1244
01:59:03.159 --> 01:59:07.370
Our Father who art in heaven,
hallowed be thy name...

1245
01:59:22.929 --> 01:59:24.764
Is it over?

1246
01:59:25.307 --> 01:59:26.891
Mm-mm.

1247
01:59:34.816 --> 01:59:36.609
Is she gonna die?

1248
01:59:41.949 --> 01:59:43.324
No.

1249
02:01:01.238 --> 02:01:03.197
You son of a bitch!

1250
02:01:09.163 --> 02:01:11.080
Take me.

1251
02:01:11.248 --> 02:01:12.540
Come into me.

1252
02:01:12.750 --> 02:01:15.752
Goddamn you, take me!

1253
02:01:16.420 --> 02:01:18.046
Take me!

1254
02:01:31.269 --> 02:01:32.728
No!

1255
02:01:42.322 --> 02:01:43.364
Mother.

1256
02:01:46.368 --> 02:01:48.118
Mother.

1257
02:01:53.583 --> 02:01:56.418
Mother.

1258
02:01:59.089 --> 02:02:00.297
Did somebody fall?

1259
02:02:00.465 --> 02:02:01.924
- The steps!
- Help!

1260
02:02:02.092 --> 02:02:03.801
Mother!

1261
02:02:05.678 --> 02:02:06.720
Mother!

1262
02:02:08.556 --> 02:02:09.599
Rags?

1263
02:02:30.996 --> 02:02:33.415
Do you want to make your confession?

1264
02:02:39.296 --> 02:02:41.339
Are you sorry for...?

1265
02:02:41.507 --> 02:02:46.136
Are you sorry for having offended God
and for all the sins of your past life?

1266
02:02:52.602 --> 02:02:54.739
<i>"Ego te absolvo in
nomine Patris..."</i>

1267
02:02:56.090 --> 02:03:00.132
<i>"...nomine Patris et Filii,
et Spiritus Sancti. Amen."</i>

1268
02:03:15.333 --> 02:03:16.750
- Where do you want this?
- What?

1269
02:03:16.918 --> 02:03:18.169
Phonograph.

1270
02:03:18.336 --> 02:03:19.545
Storage.

1271
02:03:29.055 --> 02:03:30.473
That's everything.

1272
02:03:32.560 --> 02:03:34.269
I'm gonna miss you.

1273
02:03:34.437 --> 02:03:35.812
Same here.

1274
02:03:36.355 --> 02:03:38.023
Sure you won't change your mind?

1275
02:03:53.873 --> 02:03:56.416
I found this in her room.

1276
02:04:01.088 --> 02:04:02.923
You better hurry.

1277
02:04:12.683 --> 02:04:14.519
Come on, honey, we have to get going.

1278
02:04:38.585 --> 02:04:40.378
She doesn't remember any of it.

1279
02:04:40.963 --> 02:04:42.630
That's good.

1280
02:04:46.468 --> 02:04:48.052
- All done.
- Okay.

1281
02:04:48.220 --> 02:04:49.762
Honey, this is Father Dyer.

1282
02:04:49.930 --> 02:04:52.139
- Hi, Father.
- Hello.

1283
02:04:53.016 --> 02:04:54.100
Ready, missus.

1284
02:04:56.062 --> 02:04:57.479
- Goodbye, Father.
- Goodbye.

1285
02:04:57.647 --> 02:04:59.064
I'll call you.

1286
02:05:19.877 --> 02:05:21.461
Bye.

1287
02:05:25.800 --> 02:05:27.551
- Bye, Father.
- I hope I see you again.

1288
02:05:27.719 --> 02:05:29.219
I hope so too.

1289
02:05:29.804 --> 02:05:31.680
Father Dyer?

1290
02:05:36.353 --> 02:05:38.855
I thought you'd like to keep this.

1291
02:05:47.990 --> 02:05:49.574
Why don't you keep it?

1292
02:06:54.140 --> 02:06:55.391
Lieutenant.

1293
02:06:56.434 --> 02:06:57.935
You just missed them.

1294
02:07:01.232 --> 02:07:02.732
How's the girl?

1295
02:07:03.651 --> 02:07:05.276
She seemed fine.

1296
02:07:05.986 --> 02:07:11.324
That's important.

1297
02:07:12.451 --> 02:07:14.577
Well, well...

1298
02:07:14.745 --> 02:07:17.122
...back to business, back to work.

1299
02:07:17.832 --> 02:07:20.500
- Goodbye, Father.
- Goodbye.

1300
02:07:25.214 --> 02:07:26.464
Father Dyer...

1301
02:07:28.634 --> 02:07:30.427
...do you go to films?

1302
02:07:30.594 --> 02:07:31.636
Sure.

1303
02:07:31.929 --> 02:07:35.014
Well, I got passes.

1304
02:07:35.182 --> 02:07:37.517
In fact, I got a pass to the Crest
tomorrow night.

1305
02:07:37.685 --> 02:07:38.810
Would you like to go?

1306
02:07:38.978 --> 02:07:41.731
- What's playing?
- Wuthering Heights.

1307
02:07:41.898 --> 02:07:43.399
Who's in it?

1308
02:07:44.192 --> 02:07:50.281
Heathcliff, Jackie Gleason, and in the role
of Catherine Earnshaw, Lucille Ball.

1309
02:07:51.783 --> 02:07:53.325
I've seen it.

1310
02:07:57.706 --> 02:07:59.165
Another one.

1311
02:08:00.000 --> 02:08:02.501
- Had your lunch?
- No.

